{
  "texts": [
    "Institutions could establish Ethics and Society Review boards, like Stanford Health's, to examine the societal impacts of AI projects 58.",
    "Additionally, patients and providers must be educated on safely interacting with AI, with an option to opt out of AI use when transparency around algorithm development and validation is lacking.",
    "AI vendors should be required to provide training on AI bias and algorithmic robustness to enable users to critically evaluate these technologies.",
    "Finally, healthcare providers must educate themselves on the ethical deployment of AI to protect patients and uphold the integrity of medical practice amid rapid technological advancements.",
    "Clinician leadership, coupled with robust governance and education, is crucial to ensuring AI enhances rather than undermines the quality of patient care."
  ]
}